\widowctrl\ftnbj\aenddoc\noxlattoyen\expshrtn\noultrlspc\dntblnsbdb\nospaceforul\hyphcaps0\horzdoc\dghspace120\dgvspace120\dghorigin1701\dgvorigin1984\dghshow0\dgvshow3\jcompress\viewkind1\viewscale100\nolnhtadjtbl \fet0\sectd \linex0\sectdefaultcl 
{\*\pnseclvl1\pnucrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl2\pnucltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl3\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta .}}{\*\pnseclvl4\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl5
\pndec\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl6\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl7\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl8\pnlcltr\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang
{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}{\*\pnseclvl9\pnlcrm\pnstart1\pnindent720\pnhang{\pntxtb (}{\pntxta )}}\pard\plain \s1\qc \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\b\fs32\lang2057\langfe1033\kerning32\langnp2057 Conditional Execution of Database Existence Checks
\par }\pard \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\fs32\lang2057\langfe1033\kerning32\langnp2057 Requirements
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Overview
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \tab 
\par }\pard \ql \fi720\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
There are use cases in the SUPS projects where it would be useful to be able to execute a database update when certain conditions are met. The server framework currently allows this to be done on a per table basis where the condition consists of a data ex
i
stence check, typically using the primary key of the table. However, circumstances have been found where it would be useful to conditionally update the contents of one table (using the existing mechanism) but only after a condition upon reference data has
 been evaluated. Therefore both a condition and a pre-condition are required.
\par This design does not concern itself with executing pre-conditions upon non-reference data.
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \tab \tab 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Requirements List
\par }\pard\plain \ql \fi-360\li720\ri0\nowidctlpar\tx720\faauto\rin0\lin720\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 1.\tab To be able to conditionally update 1 table given a pre-condition
 upon reference data.
\par }\pard \ql \li360\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin360\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel0\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\fs32\lang2057\langfe1033\kerning32\langnp2057 Design
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard \ql \fi720\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
It is a feature of the SUPS projects which currently have this requirement that the data required for the pre-condition exists in the XML input to the server. That is to say, the pre-condition need not query a table at the ti
me of the existence check because an appropriate query has already been performed. This is only a valid approach to take because reference data does not change over time.
\par The design is to execute an XPath based pre-condition before the database (single tab
le) existence check. This is a simpler solution than executing the pre-condition as a database query and offers better performance. It is also a more general solution in that the contents of the XML the XPath is evaluated against could come from anywhere.
 This means it need not be database based reference data. 
\par 
\par For the purposes of this design reference data may be considered to be any XML based structure or value which does not change either: 
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 1)\tab}}\pard \ql \fi-360\li1080\ri0\nowidctlpar\jclisttab\tx1080\faauto\ls1\rin0\lin1080\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 over time
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \hich\af0\dbch\af0\loch\f0 2)\tab}in a way which it is beyond the client\rquote s ability to know or control
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }{\f0 Once the condition has been evaluated an action must be taken. This can be to continue to the database check or to skip it. A third option will be added which is to throw an exception. This means that an error has occurred.
\par }\pard \ql \fi720\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\i\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard \ql \li1440\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin1440\itap0 {\i\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Configuration
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li1440\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin1440\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0 Existence checks can occur in both the query definition and method files. The syntax is the same. See \'93Query Definition Reference.doc\'94 for a full specification of the \'93CheckExists\'94
 element. Only the enhancements appear here.
\par }{\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par <CheckExists\tab condition=\'94}{\i\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 [xpath evaluating to boolean | xpath node existence check]}{\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \'94
\par \tab \tab }{\f0\highlight8 onConditionTrue}{\f0 =\'94}{\i\f0 [}{\b\i\f0 continue}{\i\f0  | skip | fail] }{\f0 \'94
\par }\pard \ql \fi720\li720\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin720\itap0 {\f0\highlight8 onConditionFalse}{\f0 =\'94}{\i\f0 [continue | }{\b\i\f0 skip}{\i\f0  | fail] }{\f0 \'94 />}{\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 
\par }\pard \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 \tab 
\par Where all attributes are optional and default values are bold. When \'93condition\'94 is a node existence check then existence maps to true and non-existence to false.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\sb240\sa60\keepn\nowidctlpar\faauto\outlinelevel1\rin0\lin0\itap0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\b\i\fs28\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Tests
\par }\trowd \trgaph108\trleft-108\trftsWidth1\trpaddl108\trpaddr108\trpaddfl3\trpaddfr3 \clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15 \cltxlrtb\clftsWidth3\clwWidth1188 \cellx1080\clvertalt\clbrdrt
\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15 \cltxlrtb\clftsWidth3\clwWidth3420 \cellx4500\clvertalt\clbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw15 \clbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw15 
\cltxlrtb\clftsWidth3\clwWidth3914 \cellx8414\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\intbl\faauto\rin0\lin0 \f1\fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\f0\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057 Number\cell Description\cell Expected result\cell 
